Responsibilities
Responsible for timely accurate and complete monthly accounting & reporting the different entities; Manage the monthly financial close process, including ensuring all costs incurred are properly recorded, reviewing journal entries, account balance reconciliations and report preparation (preparing month end reports, coordinating month-end and year-end closing processes);
Ensure the general ledger and financial statements are in compliance with all IFRS requirements;
Prepare or direct preparation of monthly, quarterly and annual financial statements and management reporting packages;
Participate in the ongoing development/establishment of accounting policies and procedures, internal control procedures surrounding financial close, operational strategies including the review and implementation of process and system changes;
Prepares analysis on monthly results and the audited annual report inclusive of the notes to the financial statements. Analyse actual to budget and forecast variances for the entities
Pro-actively initiates and structures accounting & reporting improvement processes and business practices(e.g. fast closing, intercompany reconciliation processes, invoice processing, account reconciliations, working capital management and cash collection);
Monitors and ensures correct intercompany invoicing, cost allocations;
Interacts at all levels and with budget owners or other stakeholders;
Responsible for hierarchy and scalability in chart of accounts and accuracy in the general ledger and financial statements and has ultimate authority over classification and booking of all transactions;
Prepare detailed journal entries and account analyses;
Work with the OCI Group Audit, Tax and Treasury Manager to ensure overall coordination of all financial accounting activities through annual report;
Prepare summary feedback of financial statements variances to budget;
Participates in ad hoc projects;
Develop and Maintain the ERP system (SAP) and front office system (Right Angle);
Supervises a team of 2-3 FTE including Senior accountant and Accounts Payable employee;
Contribute to internal and external audits.
